The course had weekly mini quizzes and problem sets to complete. Not terribly difficult and helps you stay on top of the content. The tutorials were very helpful and TAs got marks back quickly (1 week turnaround). Tutorial attendance counted for marks.

She was the first lecturer for BIO130 and I have to say; although she is quite monotone and her voice can be quite boring after a while, you will soon fall into a good learning  trance because of it. Her lectures slides are very organized and I guarantee you that learning only from the slides is sufficient to acquire a good mark in this class.

rComments: Professor Neumann taught the first-half of BIO130, and her lectures were organized most of the time. Although there were sections that were rushed, the information was presented effectively for most of the topics. The textbook went into unnecessary detail for the content of this course, and the lectures were detailed enough for the mid-term.

A good professor who knows her material. Lectures are very straight forward and easy to understand. I found that just studying what she said in lecture and reading over the notes I wrote from the textbook allowed me to do well on the midterm.
